s","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10035/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10035/canvas/1/da046197-01da-4afb-8e20-82c4d4e6b363","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T17:16:23.708Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>A vehemently disapproving Cyril appears in the center of the frame here while the reverse shot places Alma also in the center of the frame, setting up a battle or perhaps even a duel between the two women. This composition, both with flowers and (slightly different) light sources behind them, only reinforces that this battle seems to now be waged on even footing. Cyril’s look towards the right of the frame and Alma’s towards the left also reinforces how both are pulling in different directions.</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10035/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:681.4270355504588,123.01462155963307,500.0637901376148,538.806622706422"}}}]}]}]}